research/history/logs/agent_round_0102.stdout.log:1490:research/history/logs/agent_round_0077.stdout.log:764:research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The obvious gated one-parameter sweep is now exhausted after clean regressions on both lower LR and lower expansion, so the next least-bad informative move is to unblock the incubating `factorized_topk` family rather than introduce another fresh direction. Its only evidence so far is a `sanity_failed` prototype, which should be treated as an architecture-compatibility issue, not a quality result. A narrow code fix inside `sparsify/` to make `factorized_topk` forward/backward compatible with the runtime should recover one valid proxy measurement at K=128 under the existing strongest regime.","summary":"Fix the `factorized_topk` implementation in `sparsify/` so it passes sanity, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the current priority order: resolve the blocked sanity failure on an already-incubating family before expanding the search space again. The main risk is spending a round on implementation recovery for a family that still underperforms, but one clean run is necessary before making any architecture judgment.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The gated exploitation sweep has now tested the remaining obvious one-parameter moves at K=128 and both lower LR and lower expansion regressed cleanly.","`factorized_topk` still has no usable quality signal because its first prototype failed at sanity, so it should not be treated as an architecture-quality miss yet.","This round keeps the original `factorized_topk` proxy target and changes only the architecture code needed for forward/backward compatibility under the fixed runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `factorized_topk` run completes and beats plain `topk`, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal factorization width or activation design next.","If the repaired run completes normally but remains far behind gated, retire shallow factorization and move to a different encoder-expressivity direction such as low-rank-plus-residual or routed multi-branch designs.","If `factorized_topk` still fails sanity after the focused fix, conclude that this prototype path is currently not viable in the stack and shift effort to another architecture family with a cleaner integration path."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0102.stdout.log:1498:research/history/logs/agent_round_0077.stdout.log:870:research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0085_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The crash is a pure registration blocker: `residual_vq` is missing from the architecture whitelist in `sparsify/config.py` and likely not wired into the constructor dispatch in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`. Patch only that registration path so the unchanged `K=32, EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` proxy can instantiate.","summary":"Apply a narrow registration repair for `residual_vq` inside `sparsify/` and relaunch the exact same proxy target. Do not change the experiment recipe; only make the architecture name legal and constructible by the existing config/factory flow.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Convert the current unknown-architecture crash into a real startup/training signal for the original `residual_vq` target.","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a tight repair scoped directly to the observed `Unknown architecture` error. It preserves the original experiment exactly and avoids mixing in any new search variable.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/residual_vq.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 85 repair attempt 1 targets only the concrete registration failure for `residual_vq`; no recipe changes are allowed.","Observed blocker: `ValueError: Unknown architecture: 'residual_vq'` raised in `sparsify/config.py::__post_init__` before training starts.","Keep follow-up repairs, if needed, constrained to making the existing architecture constructible under the unchanged launcher path."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq` on quality before any further edits.","If a new concrete constructor or DDP compatibility error appears after registration is fixed, do one more pinpoint repair on the same target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive it on quality grounds rather than extending repair work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
